# RJB Contracting — WordPress -> new site redirect map (v2)
# Cloudflare Pages _redirects file. Place in the repo root (same level as index.html).
# Format: source  destination  status
#
# Cloudflare Pages pretty-URL constraint (why v2 exists):
#   1. Destinations must NEVER use .html. Pages serves /about-us.html at /about-us and
#      redirects the .html URL back to the pretty one, so a .html destination = redirect loop.
#   2. Old paths whose name matches an existing page (/about-us, /careers, /contact-us,
#      /projects, /privacy-policy) need NO rule at all — pretty-URL normalization serves
#      them natively. Only renamed or removed paths belong in this file.
# Test on the *.pages.dev preview BEFORE DNS cutover, including trailing-slash variants.

